> Heritage Centre and I&AR=E2=80=8B=E2=80=8B are planning to start a new cl=
ub in the
> institute - Heritage Club! If you are interested in knowing more about th=
e
> history of IIT Madras, institute culture in its early days and digging ou=
t
> some interesting facts from those days, then this is the place to be.
>
> *A Brief Description of Heritage Centre: *It has a repository of material
> of heritage value and historical significance representing various facets
> of the Institute. The display at the Heritage Centre provides a pictorial
> account of the events that led to the founding of IIT Madras, student lif=
e
> in the early years of the institute, the development of technological and
> other facilities and visits by distinguished people. The display also
> encompasses the campus and distinguished alumni. Also on display are a
> variety of artefacts including the foundation stone laid at the
> inauguration of the institute in 1959, a life size oil painting of Prof. =
B.
> Sengupto, the first Director of IIT Madras, and a replica of the Inter-II=
T
> Sports Trophy.' The entire collection of photographs at the Heritage Cent=
re
> has been digitised. The collection may be viewed online at
> heritage.iitm.ac.in.
>
> *A fun fact:* Located right next to Gajendra Circle, the Heritage Centre
> occupies the space where the old manual telephone exchange was situated!
>
> Heritage Centre is undergoing a major overhaul and thus wishes to make
> students as well a part of this change. Some of the club activities that
> the club members will be involved in are:
>
>    - Planning and organising club activities like Nature Walks, Heritage
>    Treasure Hunts, Heritage Quizzes, Workshops, Lectures, etc.
>    - Oral History Interviews which involve interviewing retired
>    professors of our institute who played instrumental role in early days=
 of
>    their respective departments.
>    - Preparing Heritage Guides and planning Heritage Trails (walks around
>    institute to places of historical significance)
>    - Compiling stories of major milestones in the institute's past
>    - Creating interest amongst students for institute heritage
>    - Maintaining heritage centre website and contributing content to it
>
> We are looking for students interested in the heritage of the institute,
> not necessarily having skillset to execute the above activities. It will =
be
> an opportunity to learn the skills required. If you are interested, pleas=
e
> fill this form. We are also willing to involve existing institute teams i=
n
> these activities and representatives of the same can write to
> sec_iar@smail.iitm.ac.in if they are willing to contribute to the above
> mentioned activities.
